# GRV List Enhancement - Frontend Implementation Guide

**JIRA Task:** API-704 - Include Related Summaries in GRV List

## Overview

The GRV list API endpoint has been enhanced with optional related summaries functionality. This adds two new optional query parameters and extends the response model with related GRV information while maintaining full backward compatibility.

## Changes Summary

### New Query Parameters
- `IncludeRelatedSummaries` (boolean, default: false) - Include related credit notes and parent GRV data
- `AreRelatedSummariesSortedDesc` (boolean, default: false) - Sort related credit notes by date (desc vs asc)

### Enhanced Response Model
When `IncludeRelatedSummaries=true`, the GRV list response now includes:
- `RelatedCreditNotes` - Array of credit notes related to regular GRVs
- `ParentGrv` - Parent GRV information for credit note entries

## API Usage

### Basic Usage (Unchanged)
```typescript
// Existing functionality remains identical
const response = await fetch('/api/stock/grv/list?brandId=46&storeId=10810');
const grvList = await response.json();
// Response structure is exactly the same as before
```

### Enhanced Usage with Related Summaries
```typescript
// Include related summaries with ascending date sort (default)
const response = await fetch('/api/stock/grv/list?brandId=46&storeId=10810&IncludeRelatedSummaries=true');

// Include related summaries with descending date sort
const response = await fetch('/api/stock/grv/list?brandId=46&storeId=10810&IncludeRelatedSummaries=true&AreRelatedSummariesSortedDesc=true');

const grvList = await response.json();
```

## TypeScript Interface Updates

### Enhanced GrvSummary Interface
```typescript
interface GrvSummary {
  // ... existing properties remain unchanged ...

  // New optional properties (only present when IncludeRelatedSummaries=true)
  RelatedCreditNotes?: GrvRelatedSummary[];
  ParentGrv?: GrvRelatedSummary;
}

interface GrvRelatedSummary {
  Id: number;
  GrvNumber: number;
  Status: GrvStatus;
  IsArchived: boolean;
  TransactionType: GrvTransactionType | null;
}
```

## Implementation Examples

### React Hook for GRV List with Related Summaries
```tsx
interface UseGrvListProps {
  brandId: number;
  storeId: number;
  includeRelatedSummaries?: boolean;
  sortRelatedDesc?: boolean;
}

const useGrvList = ({ 
  brandId, 
  storeId, 
  includeRelatedSummaries = false, 
  sortRelatedDesc = false 
}: UseGrvListProps) => {
  const [grvList, setGrvList] = useState<GrvSummary[]>([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);

  const fetchGrvList = useCallback(async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    try {
      const params = new URLSearchParams({
        brandId: brandId.toString(),
        storeId: storeId.toString(),
      });

      if (includeRelatedSummaries) {
        params.append('IncludeRelatedSummaries', 'true');
        if (sortRelatedDesc) {
          params.append('AreRelatedSummariesSortedDesc', 'true');
        }
      }

      const response = await fetch(`/api/stock/grv/list?${params}`);
      const data = await response.json();
      setGrvList(data);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Failed to fetch GRV list:', error);
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  }, [brandId, storeId, includeRelatedSummaries, sortRelatedDesc]);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetchGrvList();
  }, [fetchGrvList]);

  return { grvList, loading, refetch: fetchGrvList };
};
```

### Component Usage Example
```tsx
const GrvListComponent = () => {
  const [showRelated, setShowRelated] = useState(false);
  const [sortDesc, setSortDesc] = useState(false);

  const { grvList, loading } = useGrvList({
    brandId: 46,
    storeId: 10810,
    includeRelatedSummaries: showRelated,
    sortRelatedDesc: sortDesc
  });

  return (
    <div>
      <div className="controls">
        <label>
          <input 
            type="checkbox" 
            checked={showRelated}
            onChange={(e) => setShowRelated(e.target.checked)}
          />
          Include Related Summaries
        </label>

        {showRelated && (
          <label>
            <input 
              type="checkbox" 
              checked={sortDesc}
              onChange={(e) => setSortDesc(e.target.checked)}
            />
            Sort Related Descending
          </label>
        )}
      </div>

      {loading ? (
        <div>Loading...</div>
      ) : (
        <div>
          {grvList.map(grv => (
            <GrvItem key={grv.Id} grv={grv} />
          ))}
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
};

const GrvItem = ({ grv }: { grv: GrvSummary }) => (
  <div className="grv-item">
    <h3>GRV #{grv.GrvNumber}</h3>

    {/* Show related credit notes for regular GRVs */}
    {grv.RelatedCreditNotes && grv.RelatedCreditNotes.length > 0 && (
      <div className="related-credit-notes">
        <h4>Related Credit Notes:</h4>
        {grv.RelatedCreditNotes.map(creditNote => (
          <div key={creditNote.Id}>
            GRV #{creditNote.GrvNumber} - Status: {creditNote.Status}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    )}

    {/* Show parent GRV for credit note entries */}
    {grv.ParentGrv && (
      <div className="parent-grv">
        <strong>Parent GRV:</strong> #{grv.ParentGrv.GrvNumber}
      </div>
    )}
  </div>
);
```

## Important Implementation Notes

### Backward Compatibility
- **NO BREAKING CHANGES**: Existing API calls work exactly as before
- New properties are optional and only appear when explicitly requested
- Default behavior remains unchanged

### Performance Considerations
- Only request related summaries when actually needed for the UI
- The API uses optimized database queries with conditional includes
- Related data is only fetched when `IncludeRelatedSummaries=true`

### Business Logic
- **RelatedCreditNotes**: Only populated for regular GRVs (not credit notes themselves)
- **ParentGrv**: Only populated for credit note entries
- Sorting applies only to related credit notes, not the main GRV list
- Credit notes are filtered to transaction types 2 and 3 only

## Migration Guide

### For Existing Components
No changes required - existing code continues to work without modification.

### For New Features
When adding functionality that needs related GRV information:

1. Add the new query parameters to your API calls
2. Update TypeScript interfaces to include optional new properties
3. Handle the optional nature of new response properties in your UI logic
4. Consider performance implications of requesting additional data

## Testing Considerations

- Test with and without the new parameters to ensure backward compatibility
- Verify that related summaries only appear when explicitly requested
- Test sorting functionality for related credit notes
- Ensure proper handling of empty/null related data

---

